 Two questionnaires the WELCH and the "walking impairment questionnaire" (WIQ) are submitted to patients referred for vascular investigations for suspected peripheral arterial disease (PAD).

 Comparison of score to hemodynamic parameters (first goal) or maximal walking distance (MWD) on treadmill (secondary goal).

